                                                        </div>
                                                        Do journalists in China really face a tougher environment than Vietnam, Cuba, Sudan, Yemen, Laos? According to the French non-profit Reporters Without Borders (RSF), yes. China (173rd, +1) shows no sign of improving. Its prisons still hold many journalists and netizens, while increasingly unpopular Internet censorship continues to be a major obstacle to access to information. In its...  <a href="http://beijingcream.com/2013/01/china-rises-one-spot-in-latest-rsf-press-freedom-index/" title="Read China Rises One Spot In Latest Reporters Without Borders Press Freedom Index, Ranks 173 Out Of 179" class="read-more">Read more &raquo;</a><!--
